<TITLE> Fobana gears up for 2008 convention </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com) Fobana, an organisation of Bangladeshis living in North America, has formed a convening committee with Gias Ahmed and Hasanuzzaman Hassan as convener and member secretary for the 22nd North America Bangladesh Convention Fobana 2008. The committee will arrange the three-day conference of Bangladeshis living in the US and Canada, in association with America-Bangladesh Chamber of Commerce and Industries, in the first week of July, the Federation of Bangladeshi Associations in North America said in a statement Thursday. Fobana also formed an advisory committee and 26 sub-committees consisting of over 200 people to ensure more participation in the convention. Among others, Zakaria Masud Zico will work as joint convener in the convening committee, Obaidul Haq as chief coordinator, and Kazi Shakhawat Hossain Azam as co-convener. Mohammad Amin Ullah, Mohammad Hossain Khan and Mohammad Enamul Malik are advisers and Azharul Haq Milon, Md Aktar Hossain, Niaz Ahmed Jewel, Minhaz Uddin Babar and Jasim Uddin Bhuiyan are coordinators. The Fobana convention is held annually by Bangladeshi organisations in North America to commemorate the professional, sociocultural and technical achievements of Bangladeshis in their adopted countries. bd
